                      Civil Aerospace Medical Institute
                          HUMAN RESOURCES RESEARCH
   Civil Aerospace Medical Institute Logo

   Advanced ATC Systems Assessing the impact of advanced technologies on
   air traffic controller performance and workload, and investigating
   communication between pilots and air traffic controllers
   Aircrew Performance Assessing pilot performance and determining the
   performance and safety benefits associated with advanced general
   aviation (GA) displays, controls, and National Airspace System (NAS)
   concepts
   Behavioral Stressors Investigating the effects of individual,
   environmental, work schedule, and other stressors, including color
   vision deficiencies and hypoxia on ATCS and aircrew performance
   Organizational Effectiveness Investigating the effectiveness of
   organizational innovations and the relationship between work force
   psychological variables and environment variables
   Selection and Validation Evaluating approaches to job analyses,
   personnel selection and placement, and associated performance criteria
   Training and Performance Assessing the cognitive strategies and
   processes underlying skill acquisition, training programs, and
   individual and team performance
   Free Flight The Free Flight Human Factors Page-- A comprehensive source
   for Free Flight Human Factors Information
   Simulation and Re-creation Simulation capabilities and facilities


          The Human Resources Research Division (HRRD) conducts an
          integrated program of applied field and laboratory performance
          research on organizational and human factors aspects of aviation
          work environments.


